<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="gn1004a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="gn1" href="#gn1004">GN1 </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/gn1all.htm#gn1004a"> (Dzierbicki) 4(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Papa and the girls sliding downhill, astride of a toboggan: the / Grand Turk and his harem. Tightly capped and jacketted, / boots laced in deft crisscross over the flesh-warmed / tongue, the short skirt taut from the round knobs / of the knees. A white flash: a flake, a snowflake: <p class="set">And when she next doth ride abroad <br>May I be there to see!</p> </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Cf. <cite>UG</cite> 15.2815: &lsquo;lace up crisscrossed&rsquo;. The quoted verse are the <a href="https://archive.org/details/divertinghistory00cowpnyc06/page/42/mode/2up" target="_blank">last two lines</a> of William Cowper&apos;s <cite>The diverting history of John Gilpin</cite>. </mm> </dd></dl>
